article.headline: CS Northridge 70, UC Riverside 60
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) -- Joseph Frazier scored 17 points and Ian Boylan scored 15 as Cal State Northridge beat UC Riverside 70-60 Thursday night. The Matadors (17-11, 12-5 Big West Conference) were down by one, 32-31, at halftime but began the second half with a 20-4 run and kept a double-digit lead throughout the second half. The loss combined with Long Beach State's Thursday night win over Cal Poly eliminated UC Riverside (9-18, 4-13) from contention for the eighth and final spot in the Big West tournament. Larry Cunningham came off the bench to lead the Highlanders with 13 points. Davin White added 10 points for Cal State Northridge. With one game to play, the Matadors are in fourth in the Big West and have already clinched a spot in the conference tournament.
